            <scopecontent id="aspace_ffff8d55801918abfe33d2442095e634">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The series consists of a group of papers documenting the financial and business relationship of William Blake and John Linnell. The items are fully described in "New Blake Documents" by Geoffrey Keynes (<title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Times Literary Supplement</part>
                  </title>, January 9, 1943) and in <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Blake Studies: Notes on His Life and Work, in Seventeen Chapters</part>
                  </title>, by Geoffrey Keynes (London, R. Hart-Davis, 1949).</p>
            </scopecontent>
