               <odd id="aspace_d863855e8e429563b3b69ac847979aac">
                  <head>General note</head>
                  <p>Drawing measures 11.5 x 13.5 cm. Formerly laid in <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Blake's Songs of Innocence</part>
                     </title>, copy Q; see Keynes and Wolf, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>William Blake's Illuminated Books</part>
                     </title> (New York, 1953), 16.</p>
                  <p>Martin Butlin (Tate Gallery) examined the drawing on June 6, 1966, and said that it is "possibly a working over, by Linnell, of a pencil and wash drawing by Blake." Butlin identified the inscriptions on the drawing, "Timon" and "By Wm Blake," as Linnell's handwriting.</p>
               </odd>
